College_Heading: University of San Francisco (USF)
College_Summary: University of San Francisco is a private Jesuit Catholic university in California. USF currently houses over 10,000 students including 1,500+ international students. The university holds a student satisfaction rate of 96.9%. University of San Francisco programs are offered in 43 majors and 71 minors. Prospective students can also pursue education across 8 dual degrees and 7 special programs. With an acceptance rate of 70%, USF admissions exhibit a lightly selective policy. Selection to University of San Francisco will require a GPA of 3.5/4 (90%) or higher. GMAT scores are required for MBA programs and SAT scores have been made optional. The early decision deadline for admission to University of San Francisco is on November 1. The regular decision deadline for fall admission is on January 15. For spring admission, the application deadline is on November 1.
